		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Last week brought about a flurry of new and exciting changes and additions to VNBoards. With these changes, our ability to host a greater variety of features has increased dramatically. In the coming weeks, you'll be seeing even more improvements and additions to our community here, so keep your eyes open for them!  <br>  <br> To get things started, we're proud to announce the creation of the VN Insider Community Board!  <br>  <br> <span style="font-weight:bold;"><span style="color: navy;">What is the VN Insider Community Board? </span></span>Basically, this forum provides a place where we'll no longer be divided by what MMORPG or roleplaying game each other is currently playing. Any topic, which does not violate the rules of course, will be allowed and freely discussed. Simply put, it will be a place to meet new people, have some fun and relax, or even engage in a friendly debate.  <br>  <br> <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=22216">VN Insider Community Board</a> <br> Stop by and check it out!  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br> ..  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br> <span style="font-weight:bold;"><span style="color: navy;">Frequently Aksed Questions (FAQ) About Insider Boards: </span></span> <br>  <br> <span style="color: maroon;"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Question 1.1: Whaaaat? I have to be an Insider to post there?! </span></span> <br>  <br> Correctomundo!  <br>  <br> <span style="color: maroon;"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Question 1.2: Well, how come? Why not let everyone post there? </span></span> <br>  <br> Insiders help keep us alive. Because of that, we try to constantly expand our list of features to make subscription worth your while.  <br>  <br> <span style="color: maroon;"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Question 1.3: Does this mean that this board will become &quot;Insider-only?&quot; </span></span> <br>  <br> No, never. Any rumors you've heard stating otherwise are completely false. Furthermore, we're not taking away from the current access that you freely enjoy here. As we've mentioned, we're merely building up an impressive array of features that we believe will make it worth your time and money to check out.  <br>  <br> <span style="color: maroon;"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Question 1.4: An icon next to my name, access to an &quot;Insider&quot; board, plus the ability to do markup code in posts, you expect *me* to pay money for that? Other sites will give it to you for free! </span></span> <br>  <br> It depends, but do you get <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://insider.ign.com/about.html">all of this</a> with those other sites? Insider isn't just about boards, it's about the best gaming content you can find on any platform, anywhere.  <br>  <br> <span style="color: maroon;"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Question 1.5: Alright, alright. So how much does the thing cost already?  <br> </span></span> <br> - $4.95 for a monthly subscription  <br> - $11.95 for quarterly subscription  <br> - $20.00 for an annual subscription (CURRENT SPECIAL, limited time offer!)  <br>  <br> Beats the prices charged by your favorite MMORPG company, doesn't it?   <br>  <br> <span style="color: maroon;"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Question 1.6: What if I don't have a credit card? What ways are there to pay? </span></span> <br>  <br> <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://insider.ign.com/faq.html">From the official Insider FAQ:</a> <br> Monthly, quarterly and annual subscriptions to IGN Insider can be paid using a credit card issued by American Express, MasterCard or VISA. You may also pay using a debit card if the card has a MasterCard or VISA logo on its face.  <br>  <br> Annual subscriptions can be paid via PayPal. We also accept payment for annual subscriptions using a check, money order or cash (U.S. dollars only). If paying with cash, payment must be sent via certified mail. Please note: Monthly and quarterly subscriptions can not be paid for using PayPal, check, money order or cash.  <br>  <br> We also offer sponsorship opportunities for quarterly and annual subscriptions to IGN Insider. To qualify for a sponsored subscription, you must join one of IGN's partners' programs from our website. Once our partner approves your application they will notify us to activate your IGN Insider subscription. To learn more and to view all of IGN's current partners, <a class=BoardRowBLink href="https://smy.ign.com/my/sb?uoaction=displaySubSponsors&amp;show_close=true">please click here. </a> <br>  <br> <span style="color: maroon;"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Question 1.7: Is this post just an advertisement? </span></span> <br>  <br> Yes and no. Emphasis placed on the latter.   <br>  <br> <span style="color: maroon;"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Question 1.8: What if I think this is all just a big crock?</span></span>  <br>  <br> A forum where no one ever disagreed with each other would be pretty boring now, wouldn't it?   <br>  <br> <span style="color: maroon;"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Question 1.9: What were those links again? </span></span> <br>  <br> <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://insider.ign.com/faq.html">- Insider FAQ </a> <br> <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://insider.ign.com/about.html">- Insider Benefits </a>
